2
00:00:02.190 --> 00:00:04.100
The Great Pirate Era...

3
00:00:04.100 --> 00:00:09.070
has proven to be a more tumultuous storm
than the World Government expected.

4
00:00:10.910 --> 00:00:18.120
The figures in the eye of this
relentless tempest are…

5
00:00:19.990 --> 00:00:21.830
Monkey D. Luffy...

6
00:00:23.130 --> 00:00:25.120
and the Straw Hat Pirates!

7
00:00:27.500 --> 00:00:31.380
To confront the furious Great Pirate Era,

8
00:00:31.380 --> 00:00:35.850
fifty world leaders have come together
for this quadrennial conference:

9
00:00:36.720 --> 00:00:39.930
the Reverie, which will commence shortly.

10
00:00:44.690 --> 00:00:48.340
Now is a time of great change.

11
00:00:53.280 --> 00:00:59.580
A Beautiful World

12
00:00:59.580 --> 00:01:02.920
Marines

13
00:01:04.090 --> 00:01:08.050
Here stands Fleet Admiral Sakazuki's
new Marine Headquarters:

14
00:01:08.050 --> 00:01:10.260
New Marineford.

15
00:01:11.180 --> 00:01:14.300
Two years ago, the forces
of Marine Headquarters

16
00:01:14.300 --> 00:01:19.060
triumphed over the Whitebeard Pirates
during the Summit War.

17
00:01:19.060 --> 00:01:24.190
However, the battlefield of Marineford
suffered massive devastation.

18
00:01:24.810 --> 00:01:28.570
Though Marineford had long
been the seat of justice,

19
00:01:28.570 --> 00:01:32.530
the World Government built
an even more impregnable fortress

20
00:01:32.530 --> 00:01:35.280
to prepare for the rising fury of the Pirate Era.

21
00:01:36.080 --> 00:01:40.580
This new fort of justice at
the entry to the New World

22
00:01:40.580 --> 00:01:43.460
is New Marineford.

23
00:01:47.170 --> 00:01:50.550
Fujitora is in Mary Geoise?!

24
00:01:50.550 --> 00:01:52.380
Y-Yes, sir!

25
00:01:53.050 --> 00:01:56.140
I told him to stay away
from all Marine bases...

26
00:01:56.140 --> 00:01:59.520
until he brings me
Straw Hat's and Law's heads!

27
00:01:59.520 --> 00:02:04.730
I won't hear any lip about how he forgot
what I told him on Dressrosa!

28
00:02:04.730 --> 00:02:06.730
Oh, scary!

29
00:02:06.730 --> 00:02:10.320
How dare that mongrel come slinking back!

30
00:02:10.320 --> 00:02:14.450
Y-Yes, sir, we all remember what you told him.

31
00:02:14.450 --> 00:02:16.530
Then why didn't you send him packing?!

32
00:02:16.870 --> 00:02:18.240
Well...

33
00:02:18.240 --> 00:02:21.620
we had no rebuttal for his
airtight counterargument...

34
00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:27.750
This is not a Marine base.

35
00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:30.250
That's just a technicality!

36
00:02:30.250 --> 00:02:32.510
That damned vagabond monk!

37
00:02:36.510 --> 00:02:37.850
Oh?

38
00:02:37.850 --> 00:02:40.060
Difficult job, isn't it...

39
00:02:40.930 --> 00:02:42.680
Fleet Admiral?

40
00:02:42.680 --> 00:02:44.640
S-Sengoku...!

41
00:02:45.850 --> 00:02:48.560
Butt out, you semi-retired has-been!

42
00:02:51.570 --> 00:02:53.820
Who else has gone to Mary Geoise?!

43
00:02:53.820 --> 00:02:57.200
A-Admiral Ryokugyu!

44
00:02:57.200 --> 00:02:59.280
Ryokugyu, huh?

45
00:02:59.280 --> 00:03:01.160
Contact him immediately!

46
00:03:01.160 --> 00:03:01.950
Yes, sir!

47
00:03:02.620 --> 00:03:05.870
Despite New Marineford's updated location,

48
00:03:05.870 --> 00:03:11.670
it remains as gatekeeper to the Holy Land
of Mary Geoise, home of the Celestial Dragons.

49
00:03:12.260 --> 00:03:18.760
The place where the Summit War
was fought is now the G-1 branch.

50
00:03:18.760 --> 00:03:24.730
The two Marine bases are situated on both sides
of the Red Line to protect Mary Geoise against invasion.

